Range-String

An suite of objected-oriented modules for string and integer set arithmetics.

Range::String is able to parse complex range arithmetic expressions such as 
scope, subtraction, intersection, etc.

Version 0.01 is a pure Perl implementation.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Range::Integer

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Range-Integer

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Range-Integer

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Range-Integer

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Range-Integer/


